description:
Add filtering support for listing tasks awaiting human attention:

```bash
# All ticks awaiting human action
tk list --awaiting

# Only ticks awaiting approval
tk list --awaiting approval

# Ticks awaiting approval or review
tk list --awaiting approval,review
```

May need to implement locally in ticks client if tk CLI doesn't support:
```go
func (c *Client) ListAwaitingTasks(epicID string, awaitingTypes ...string) ([]Task, error) {
    tasks, err := c.ListTasks(epicID)
    if err \!= nil {
        return nil, err
    }

    var result []Task
    for _, t := range tasks {
        if t.IsAwaitingHuman() {
            if len(awaitingTypes) == 0 || contains(awaitingTypes, t.GetAwaitingType()) {
                result = append(result, t)
            }
        }
    }
    return result, nil
}
```

Acceptance criteria:
- [ ] --awaiting filter works on tk list
- [ ] Can filter by specific types (comma-separated)
- [ ] ListAwaitingTasks method added to client
